South Africa’s President Cyril Ramaphosa said on Wednesday casinos, cinemas, personal care services and accommodation will be allowed to operate as the country further eases coronavirus lockdown restrictions. Ramaphosa added during his televised address to the nation that restaurants will now be allowed to offer sit-down services. A date of when these sectors will be re-opened will be announced in due course, he said. WATCH/READ: LIVE ARCHIVE: Lockdown Day 83 – President announces easing of some Level 3 restrictions